wikipedia_page.main: Arthur Wilkinson (28 December 1872 – unknown) was an English first-class cricketer active 1894–95 who played for Nottinghamshire. He was born in Nottingham.

response: Arthur Wilkinson (3 September 1919 – 1968) was a British orchestral composer and arranger.  He began composing while serving in the Royal Air Force during World War II, and made many contributions to film, stage shows and television.
